---

<html lang="en" data-theme="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>mosaigo — Event-Driven Pipeline Framework for Go</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="mosaigo is a modular, event-driven pipeline framework for Go. Compose type-safe processing steps, observe everything in real time, and swap any piece without touching the rest."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" />
    <style is:inline>
      :root {
        --primary: #2A7FBF;
        --deep: #1B4F7A;
        --light: #6DB3E0;
        --accent: #C8982A;
        --error: #B53030;
        --success: #3A8F5C;
        --muted: #6B6B78;
        --bg: #1a1a22;
        --bg-card: #22222c;
        --bg-code: #1e1e28;
        --text: #e4e4ea;
        --text-secondary: #9d9da8;
        --text-muted: #6B6B78;
        --border: #2e2e3a;
        --border-hover: #3e3e4e;
      }
      * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
      body {
        font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.65;
        font-size: 15px;
      }

      /* NAV */
      .topnav {
        position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 56px;
        background: #16161e; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 0 24px; z-index: 100;
      }
      .topnav-logo {
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
        text-decoration: none; color: var(--text);
        font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-right: 32px;
      }
      .logo-icon {
        width: 28px; height: 28px; background: var(--primary);
        border-radius: 6px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
      }
      .logo-icon::after {
        content: ''; width: 12px; height: 12px;
        background: var(--accent); border-radius: 2px; transform: rotate(45deg);
      }
      .topnav-links { display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: center; }
      .topnav-link {
        color: var(--text-secondary); text-decoration: none;
        font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 500; transition: color 0.15s;
      }
      .topnav-link:hover { color: var(--text); }
      .topnav-right { margin-left: auto; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; }
      .gh-link { color: var(--text-secondary); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500; }
      .gh-link:hover { color: var(--text); }
      .license-badge {
        font-size: 0.68rem; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 4px;
        background: rgba(58,143,92,0.15); color: var(--success); font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* HERO */
      .hero {
        padding: 120px 24px 80px; text-align: center;
        position: relative; overflow: hidden;
      }
      .hero::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
        background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 0%, rgba(42,127,191,0.08) 0%, transparent 70%);
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .hero-badge {
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
        padding: 4px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--border);
        font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .hero-badge .dot { width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--success); }
      .hero h1 {
        font-size: 3.4rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.04em;
        line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 16px; max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;
      }
      .hero h1 .accent { color: var(--primary); }
      .hero .tagline {
        font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-secondary);
        max-width: 580px; margin: 0 auto 32px; line-height: 1.5;
      }
      .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 24px; }
      .btn {
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
        padding: 11px 24px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.92rem;
        font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.15s;
      }
      .btn-primary { background: var(--primary); color: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--primary); }
      .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--deep); border-color: var(--deep); }
      .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: var(--text); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); }
      .hero-install {
        display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
        background: var(--bg-code); border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 18px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.86rem; color: var(--text);
      }
      .hero-install .prompt { color: var(--accent); user-select: none; }

      /* SECTIONS */
      .section { padding: 80px 24px; max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .section-label {
        font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px;
      }
      .section h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .section .section-desc {
        font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-secondary);
        max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 36px; line-height: 1.5;
      }

      /* CARDS */
      .diff-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
      .diff-card {
        background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 12px; padding: 28px; transition: border-color 0.15s;
      }
      .diff-card:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); }
      .diff-icon {
        width: 44px; height: 44px; border-radius: 10px;
        display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
        font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 16px;
      }
      .diff-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .diff-card p { font-size: 0.86rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.55; }

      /* CODE */
      .code-showcase { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 32px; align-items: start; }
      .code-text h3 { font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .code-text p { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .code-text ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
      .code-text li {
        padding: 6px 0; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-secondary);
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
      }
      .code-text li::before {
        content: ''; width: 6px; height: 6px;
        border-radius: 50%; background: var(--primary); flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      .code-block {
        background: var(--bg-code); border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px 24px; overflow-x: auto;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.65;
      }
      .code-block .kw { color: var(--primary); }
      .code-block .st { color: var(--accent); }
      .code-block .cm { color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic; }
      .code-block .fn { color: #d4a0e0; }
      .code-header {
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 8px 16px;
        background: var(--border); border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
        font-size: 0.76rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      }
      .code-header + .code-block { border-radius: 0 0 10px 10px; margin-top: 0; }

      /* ARCHITECTURE */
      .arch-visual { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .arch-layer {
        padding: 18px 24px; border-radius: 10px;
        text-align: center; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem;
      }
      .arch-layer .desc { font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.8rem; opacity: 0.8; margin-top: 3px; }
      .arch-arrow { text-align: center; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 2px 0; }
      .arch-caption { text-align: center; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 20px; }

      /* STATS */
      .stats-row {
        display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 48px; padding: 48px 24px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      .stat { text-align: center; }
      .stat .num { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--primary); }
      .stat .label { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 2px; }

      /* ITERATE */
      .eco-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
      .eco-card {
        background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; transition: border-color 0.15s;
      }
      .eco-card:hover { border-color: var(--border-hover); }
      .eco-badge {
        display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;
        font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 12px;
      }
      .eco-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .eco-card p { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

      /* PRINCIPLES */
      .principle-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
      .principle { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: start; }
      .principle-num {
        font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary);
        opacity: 0.5; line-height: 1; min-width: 28px;
      }
      .principle h4 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 3px; }
      .principle p { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

      /* CTA */
      .cta { text-align: center; padding: 80px 24px; }
      .cta h2 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
      .cta p {
        color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.05rem;
        margin-bottom: 28px; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;
      }

      /* FOOTER */
      .footer {
        padding: 32px 24px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        text-align: center; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.82rem;
      }
      .footer a { color: var(--text-secondary); text-decoration: none; }
      .footer a:hover { color: var(--text); }
      .footer-links { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }

      @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .diff-grid, .eco-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .principle-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .code-showcase { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
        .stats-row { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 24px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="topnav">
      <a href="/" class="topnav-logo">
        <div class="logo-icon"></div>
        mosaigo
      </a>
      <div class="topnav-links">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="topnav-link">Docs</a>
        <a href="/mosoptics/" class="topnav-link">mosoptics</a>
        <a href="/eyemia/" class="topnav-link">EyeMia</a>
      </div>
      <div class="topnav-right">
        <a href="https://github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo" class="gh-link">GitHub</a>
        <span class="license-badge">Apache-2.0</span>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-badge"><span class="dot"></span> Open source &middot; Apache 2.0 &middot; Pure Go</div>
      <h1>Build pipelines like <span class="accent">mosaics</span></h1>
      <p class="tagline">mosaigo is a modular, event-driven pipeline framework for Go. Compose type-safe processing steps, observe everything in real time, and swap any piece without touching the rest.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo" class="btn btn-secondary">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-install">
        <span class="prompt">$</span> go get github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo@latest
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Why mosaigo</div>
      <h2>Every step is a tile. Together, they're a picture.</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Most pipeline frameworks force you to choose between flexibility and type safety. Mosaigo gives you both — with built-in observability and zero-allocation hot paths.</p>
      <div class="diff-grid">
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(42,127,191,0.12);color:var(--primary);">&#9881;</div>
          <h3>Type-Safe Generic Steps</h3>
          <p><code>TypedEngineStep[TIN, TOUT]</code> catches payload mismatches at compile time. Every step declares its input, output, config schema, and metadata through <code>StepDef</code>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(200,152,42,0.12);color:var(--accent);">&#9670;</div>
          <h3>Self-Describing Pipeline</h3>
          <p>Steps register themselves with full metadata. The framework auto-generates step catalogs, validates pipeline wiring before execution, and serializes issues to REST/WebSocket.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(58,143,92,0.12);color:var(--success);">&#9201;</div>
          <h3>Zero-Alloc Hot Path</h3>
          <p>Designed for real-time: pre-allocated buffers, zero-copy payload passing. Init() allocates, Process() is allocation-free, Close() releases. 120fps camera pipelines, not batch ETL.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(109,179,224,0.12);color:var(--light);">&#9783;</div>
          <h3>Built-In Observability</h3>
          <p>Every step automatically tracks latency via <code>MarkTime</code>. Topic pub/sub enables multi-engine architectures. Studio UI shows live pipeline graphs with per-step timing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(181,48,48,0.12);color:var(--error);">&#8644;</div>
          <h3>Hexagonal by Default</h3>
          <p>Steps never import infrastructure. Assembly happens at the top. Ports define contracts, adapters are swappable by config. Your step doesn't know about routers or drivers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-card">
          <div class="diff-icon" style="background:rgba(107,107,120,0.12);color:var(--text-secondary);">&#9874;</div>
          <h3>Config, YAML, or API</h3>
          <p>Three ways to build pipelines: programmatic Go API, YAML factory from the step registry, or web service payload via REST/WebSocket. Same validation, same steps.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">In practice</div>
      <h2>A pipeline in 15 lines</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Build, validate, and run. Every step comes from the registry, wired by the engine, observable by default.</p>
      <div class="code-showcase">
        <div>
          <div class="code-header">main.go</div>
          <div class="code-block" set:html={`<span class="kw">package</span> main

<span class="kw">import</span> (
    <span class="st">"github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo/engine"</span>
    <span class="st">"github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo/mos"</span>
)

<span class="kw">func</span> <span class="fn">main</span>() {
    <span class="cm">// Build from registered steps</span>
    eng := engine.<span class="fn">NewBuilder</span>(<span class="st">"my-pipeline"</span>).
        <span class="fn">AddByName</span>(<span class="st">"capture.session"</span>).
        <span class="fn">AddByName</span>(<span class="st">"vision.detect.ultraface"</span>).
        <span class="fn">AddByName</span>(<span class="st">"vision.gaze.l2cs"</span>).
        <span class="fn">Build</span>()

    <span class="cm">// Validate the full pipeline — all issues, not fail-fast</span>
    <span class="kw">if</span> issues := eng.<span class="fn">Validate</span>(); <span class="fn">len</span>(issues) &gt; <span class="st">0</span> {
        mos.<span class="fn">LogIssues</span>(issues)
        <span class="kw">return</span>
    }

    eng.<span class="fn">Run</span>() <span class="cm">// blocks, processes frames, observable via Studio</span>
}`} />
        </div>
        <div class="code-text" style="padding-top:32px;">
          <h3>What's happening here</h3>
          <p>Steps are resolved from the global <code>StepDef</code> registry by name. Each step was registered at init time with its config type, I/O payloads, and metadata.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Steps compile in — no dynamic plugins, no reflection at runtime</li>
            <li>The validator walks the full pipeline and collects every issue</li>
            <li>Process() is the hot path — zero allocation, MarkTime instrumented</li>
            <li>Topic pub/sub enables multi-engine architectures at different frame rates</li>
            <li>Config overridable: defaults &lt; YAML &lt; env var &lt; runtime API</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" style="text-align:center;">
      <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
      <h2>Metadata-driven composition</h2>
      <p class="section-desc" style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">Every step describes itself completely. The framework uses that metadata to validate pipelines, generate catalogs, serve config schemas, and power the Studio UI — all automatically.</p>
      <div class="arch-visual">
        <div class="arch-layer" style="background:rgba(200,152,42,0.15);color:var(--accent);border:1px solid rgba(200,152,42,0.3);">
          Your Product <span class="desc">— Compose steps, configure via YAML/API, ship</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">assembles &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer" style="background:rgba(42,127,191,0.15);color:var(--primary);border:1px solid rgba(42,127,191,0.3);">
          Domain Step Libraries <span class="desc">— CV, IoT, ETL, audio, or your own — all TypedEngineStep</span>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-arrow">built on &#8595;</div>
        <div class="arch-layer" style="background:rgba(27,79,122,0.3);color:var(--light);border:1px solid rgba(27,79,122,0.5);">
          mosaigo <span class="desc">— Engine, pipeline, typed steps, topics, config, validation, Studio</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="arch-caption">mosaigo is domain-agnostic. Your step libraries bring the domain knowledge. mosaigo brings the composition, observability, and runtime.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">0</div><div class="label">CGo in the core</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">3</div><div class="label">Pipeline construction modes</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">0</div><div class="label">Allocations in Process()</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">100%</div><div class="label">Steps self-describing</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">Apache-2.0</div><div class="label">License</div></div>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Iterate fast</div>
      <h2>Build alternatives, not commitments</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Mosaigo is built for experimentation. Don't pick an algorithm — try three. Steps are cheap to write, fast to swap, and the framework measures everything so you can compare empirically.</p>
      <div class="eco-grid">
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge" style="background:rgba(42,127,191,0.15);color:var(--primary);">compose</div>
          <h3>Snap steps together</h3>
          <p>Each step is a single-purpose tile with typed input and output. Rearrange, replace, or duplicate any tile without touching the rest. The pipeline is a composition, not a monolith.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge" style="background:rgba(200,152,42,0.15);color:var(--accent);">configure</div>
          <h3>Runtime-swappable config</h3>
          <p>Every step declares its config schema via struct tags. Override via YAML, environment variables, or runtime API — no recompile. Defaults &lt; file &lt; env &lt; API, always.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="eco-card">
          <div class="eco-badge" style="background:rgba(58,143,92,0.15);color:var(--success);">measure</div>
          <h3>See what's actually happening</h3>
          <p>MarkTime on every step. Per-step latency in the API. Topic throughput metrics. Studio dashboard. You can't improve what you can't see — mosaigo makes sure you see everything.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">Values</div>
      <h2>What mosaigo believes</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">These aren't rules to follow — they're the reason the framework exists.</p>
      <div class="principle-grid">
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">01</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Composition over configuration</h4>
            <p>Pipelines are assembled from independent steps, not configured from a mega-YAML. Each step does one thing. Swap, reorder, or duplicate any tile without touching the others.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">02</div>
          <div>
            <h4>The compiler is your first reviewer</h4>
            <p>Go generics catch payload mismatches at build time. If your step expects <code>[TIN]</code> and the previous step outputs something else, you know before you run.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">03</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Metadata is not optional</h4>
            <p>Every step declares its name, config schema, I/O types, and required metadata via <code>StepDef</code>. This powers validation, the step catalog, Studio, and the API.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">04</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Steps don't know where they live</h4>
            <p>A step works with domain types, not infrastructure. Ports define contracts. Adapters are swappable. Testing is trivial.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">05</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Fail comprehensively, not fast</h4>
            <p>The validator walks the full pipeline and collects every issue into a serializable list. You see all the problems at once — not one at a time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-num">06</div>
          <div>
            <h4>Stdlib unless proven otherwise</h4>
            <p><code>slog</code>, not logrus. <code>net/http</code>, not fiber. Every dependency is evaluated against a strict rubric.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Ready to build?</h2>
      <p>Read the getting started guide, browse the step catalog, or jump straight into the code.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/getting-started/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the Docs</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/mosaigoio/mosaigo" class="btn btn-secondary">Star on GitHub</a>
